HELP EXPRSTA                                                     A.Sloman 1982

-- EXPRESSIONS and STATEMENTS -----------------------------------------------

POP-11 programs consist of sequences of statements. Statements are normally
separated by semicolons (see HELP *SEMICOLON). There are various kinds of
statements that you can make in POP11 - see the appropriate HELP files:

    *PROCDEFINE  - for defining procedures
    *VARS        - for declaring variables
    *EXPRASS     - for expressions and assignments
    *LOOPS       - for repeating some actions a number of times
    *CONDITIONALS - for doing something only if some condition is true
    *GOTO        - for transferring control within a procedure (not
                    recommended)
